name: HttpResponse
description: Use the HttpResponse class to handle the HTTP response returned by the Http class.

getbody().name: getBody
getbody().description: Retrieves the body returned in the response.

getbodyasblob().name: getBodyAsBlob
getbodyasblob().description: Retrieves the body returned in the response as a Blob.

getbodydocument().name: getBodyDocument
getbodydocument().description: Retrieves the body returned in the response as a DOM document.

getheader(string).name: getHeader
getheader(string).description: Retrieves the contents of the response header.

getheaderkeys().name: getHeaderKeys
getheaderkeys().description: Retrieves an array of header keys returned in the response.

getstatus().name: getStatus
getstatus().description: Retrieves the status message returned for the response.

getstatuscode().name: getStatusCode
getstatuscode().description: Retrieves the value of the status code returned in the response.

getxmlstreamreader().name: getXmlStreamReader
getxmlstreamreader().description: Returns an XmlStreamReader that parses the body of the callout response.

setbody(string).name: setBody
setbody(string).description: Specifies the body returned in the response.

setbodyasblob(blob).name: setBodyAsBlob
setbodyasblob(blob).description: Specifies the body returned in the response using a Blob.

setheader(string,string).name: setHeader
setheader(string,string).signature: public Void setHeader(String key, String value)
setheader(string,string).overrideSignature: public override Void setHeader(String key, String value)
setheader(string,string).description: Specifies the contents of the response header.

setstatus(string).name: setStatus
setstatus(string).description: Specifies the status message returned in the response.

setstatuscode(integer).name: setStatusCode
setstatuscode(integer).description: Specifies the value of the status code returned in the response.
